
<div class="banner" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.4),rgba(0,0,0,0.4)), url('https://res.cloudinary.com/wectcorp/image/upload/v1683229282/qlou0vuhodllztack5hl.jpg');">
  <div class="container">
    <h1><strong>Only takes 3 Minutes</strong></h1>
    <p>Start-Up Marketplace</p>
  </div>
</div>


<%= simple_form_for(@criterium, data: { controller: "multi-step-form" }) do |f| %>

  <!-- First question: Search status -->
  <div class="form-page" data-multi-step-form-target="formPage">
    <div class="container-small">
      <%= f.label :search_status, 'Click =>' %>
    </div>
    <%= f.hidden_field :search_status %>
   <!-- Display the header card for the status question -->
    <div class="button-group  ">
      <div class="onboaring_margin_negative">
        <div class="container-small">
          <div class="card-header">
            <%= image_tag "brain.png", class: "avatar-medium" %>
            <div class="card-header-info">
              <h2>Share Your Job Search Status! üöÄ</h2>
              <p>We're all about making your job search experience more personalized and enjoyable! Let us know where you're at in your job-hunting journey, and we'll tailor the process to suit your needs. Choose the option that fits your current situation the best!</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="nav-answers-buttons">
        <% Criterium::SEARCH_STATUS.each do |status| %>
        <div class="">
          <div class="btn-rainbow-container">
            <%= link_to status, "#", class: "btn-rainbow-link", data: { action: "click->multi-step-form#nextPage", answer_value: status, param_name: "search_status" } %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Second question: Notice period -->
  <div class="form-page" data-multi-step-form-target="formPage">
    <div class="container-small">
     <%= f.label :notice_period, label: 'Click =>' %>
    </div>
    <%= f.hidden_field :notice_period %>
     <!-- Display the header card for the notice-period question -->
    <div class="button-group  ">
      <div class="onboaring_margin_negative">
        <div class="container-small">
          <div class="card-header">
            <%= image_tag "brain.png", class: "avatar-medium" %>
            <div class="card-header-info">
              <h2>Notice Period? No Problem! ‚è∞</h2>
              <p>To help you find the perfect job opportunity, let us know if you have a notice period to serve. This way, we can present you with job openings that align with your availability. Just tell us when you'd be ready to embark on a new adventure!</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class=" nav-answers-buttons">
        <% Criterium::NOTICE_PERIOD.each do |period| %>
        <div class=" ">
          <div class="btn-rainbow-container">
            <%= link_to period, "#", class: "btn-rainbow-link", data: { action: "click->multi-step-form#nextPage", answer_value: period, param_name: "notice_period" } %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Third question: Location -->
  <div class="form-page" data-multi-step-form-target="formPage">
    <div class="onboaring_margin_negative">
      <div class="container-small">
        <div class="card-header">
          <%= image_tag "brain.png", class: "avatar-medium" %>
          <div class="card-header-info">
            <h2>Location, Location, Location! üåç</h2>
            <p>We're here to help you find the best job opportunities, no matter where you're based. Let us know your current location, and we'll make sure to tailor your job search accordingly. Are you open to remote work? We've got that covered too!

            Scroll below for more details..</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <div class="accordion-space">
          <div class="accordion px-3" id="accordionExample">
            <h2>Q&A</h2>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                Remote Friendly
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  Another remote working option is to work for a company that is ‚Äúremote-friendly.‚Äù This essentially means your company is open to occasional remote work, but expects you to be in the office the majority of the time.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Hybrid (WFH + In-office)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  As the pandemic begins to ease in some parts of the world, many people and companies are opting for a hybrid opportunity. Typically, this means an arrangement between employers and workers where they agree on set ‚Äúin office‚Äù days and other ‚ÄúWFH‚Äù days.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                  Fully Remote
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  Finally, there‚Äôs fully remote work. When you get a 100% remote job, you‚Äôre most likely not expected to ever come to the office.
                  In fact, you may never even meet the people you work with face-to-face. Many remote workers don‚Äôt even live in the same country as their employers.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <br>
          <br>
          <br>
          </div>
        </div>

        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer_onboarding_section3 ">
      <div class="container-small">
        <p>Type here location</p>
        <%= f.input :location, label: false, placeholder: "E.G. Paris" %>
        <p>Select Remote work type</p>
        <%= f.input :remote_work_type, label: false, collection:   Criterium::REMOTE_WORK_TYPE %>
      </div>
      <br>
      <br>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Fourth question: Salary grid -->
  <div class="form-page" data-multi-step-form-target="formPage">
    <div class="onboaring_margin_negative">
      <div class="container-small">
        <div class="card-header">
          <%= image_tag "brain.png", class: "avatar-medium" %>
          <div class="card-header-info">
            <h2>Find Jobs That Pay Your Worth! üåü</h2>
            <p>Share your yearly salary expectations with us to help find the perfect job that meets your financial goals.
            </p>
             <p>Unsure about the numbers? Choose 'Open' and we'll explore together. Keep in mind that it doesn't have to be in your local currency ‚Äì just pick a range that suits your needs.

            Scroll below to learn more.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>

        <div class="accordion-space">
          <div class="accordion px-3" id="accordionExample">
            <h2>Q&A</h2>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                  Why are the salary options in Euros?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  We're using Euros as a standard currency to simplify the process for everyone. You can still pick a range that matches your desired earnings in your local currency's equivalent.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                  Will my salary expectation be shared with companies?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  Yep, we do share your salary expectations with companies. But don't worry, it helps them understand your worth and find opportunities that match your financial goals. It's all about creating a perfect fit!.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                  What if I'm unsure about my salary expectation?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  No problem! Just select the "open" option, and we'll help you figure out your market value. Our goal is to make sure you find the right opportunity that aligns with your skills and experience.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                  Is it wise to aim high with my salary expectation?
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  It's good to know your worth, but remember, companies can accurately benchmark your market value. So, be wise with your expectations! That way, you won't miss out on great opportunities. And keep in mind, salary negotiations are always on the table once you're in the process with fantastic companies.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
          </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
        <br>
      </div>

      <div class="footer_onboarding_section3 ">

        <div class="container-small">
            <p>Select your salary grid</p>
            <%= f.input :salary_grid, label: false, collection:   Criterium::SALARY_GRID %>
        </div>
        <br>
        <br>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Fifth question: Position -->
  <div class="form-page" data-multi-step-form-target="formPage">
    <div class="onboaring_margin_negative">
      <div class="container-small">
        <div class="card-header">
          <%= image_tag "brain.png", class: "avatar-medium" %>
          <div class="card-header-info">
            <h2>What Is Your Target Job?üéØ</h2>
            <p>Tell us the job you have in mind, and we'll find fantastic opportunities that fit your career objectives. Being specific helps us refine our search to bring you closer to the perfect position. Let's embark on this exciting journey together!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <div class="footer_onboarding_section3 ">

        <div class="container-small">
          <p><strong>[MANDATORY] </strong>Select your desired position</p>
          <%= f.input :position_id, label: false, collection: Position.all, label_method: lambda { |position| position.position_name } %>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<div class="footer_onboarding_section3">

  <div class="navigation container-nav-buttons ">
    <%= link_to "Previous", "#", class: "nav-buttons-onboarding-back", data: { multi_step_form_target: "prevButton", action: "click->multi-step-form#prevPage" } %>
    <%= link_to "Next", "#", class: "nav-buttons-onboarding-next", data: { multi_step_form_target: "nextButton", action: "click->multi-step-form#nextPage" } %>

    <div class="">
      <%= f.submit 'Next', class: "nav-buttons-onboarding-next", data: { multi_step_form_target: "submitButton" } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<% end %>
